  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solution Description&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Effectively control change by capturing sufficient information for change requests and standardizing the SCM policies&#xD;
    and procedures to which the team must adhere.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Symptoms&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following symptoms indicate a need for improvement in controlling change:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Change requests (of any type) are not captured. There is no process or set of policies in place describing who&#xD;
        should receive requests, who can approve requests,&amp;nbsp;and the process to approve or reject them.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Change Requests get&amp;nbsp;lost during the request / approval process.&amp;nbsp;The team&amp;nbsp;cannot track who&#xD;
        requested&amp;nbsp;each change and which part(s) of the system are affected.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Change requests are manually processed, resulting in an ineffective change request process.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Unable to determine which version is the latest, which version is deployed, what changes are made to this version &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                No easy way for the team&amp;nbsp;to roll back to the previous version if something goes wrong.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Parallel development is not possible.&amp;nbsp; It takes&amp;nbsp;the team&amp;nbsp;lots of time to merge artifacts&amp;nbsp;in&#xD;
        order&amp;nbsp;to work in parallel.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Not&amp;nbsp;effectively managing appropriate approvals for different type of change requests.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        No&amp;nbsp;builds baseline which enables&amp;nbsp;the team&amp;nbsp;to associate a stable source code configuration&#xD;
        with&amp;nbsp;a build.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Problems&amp;nbsp;managing and supporting multiple versions (variants, revisions) of applications at the same time.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solutions&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Adopt Team Change Management or Formal Change Management depending on the level of formality&amp;nbsp;needed&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Integrate change management with configuration management.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Make SCM more effective by adopting&amp;nbsp;an SCM tool and deploying application lifecycle management&amp;nbsp;to govern&#xD;
        the SCM process.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearCase&amp;reg; (including CCz)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; ClearQuest&amp;reg;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg; (including&amp;nbsp;RTCz and RTCi)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; RequisitePro&amp;reg;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; DOORS&amp;reg;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; BuildForge&amp;reg;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Requirements management tools can also support this solution.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
